      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      369.52,
      547.6,
      382.8
    ],
    "text": "Assistant Director and P. Padma Wahasala Zonal Director of Education Puttalam as his",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      390.16,
      544.7,
      403.44
    ],
    "text": "witnesses. By written communication, the Secretary of the Public Service Commission (North-",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      410.92,
      547.66,
      424.2
    ],
    "text": "Western Province) had informed that special permission is not necessary to call witnesses;",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      431.58,
      300.53,
      444.86
    ],
    "text": "therefore, the inquiring Officer should decide.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      472.98,
      547.44,
      486.26
    ],
    "text": "The learned High Court Judge had observed that there was no need to call the Senior Officers",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      493.74,
      547.61,
      507.02
    ],
    "text": "when their juniors were present. The Appellant had the opportunity to cross-examine and establish",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      514.38,
      136.94,
      527.66
    ],
    "text": "his defence.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      555.78,
      547.44,
      569.06
    ],
    "text": "In this country, the measure to find someone guilty in a criminal case is beyond reasonable ground",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      576.54,
      547.65,
      589.82
    ],
    "text": "until the prosecution proves that the accused is treated as an innocent party. Even though the",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      597.21,
      547.65,
      610.49
    ],
    "text": "domestic inquiries are different and the inquiring officers are not learned in the law, they must",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      617.97,
      547.66,
      631.25
    ],
    "text": "have a similar approach when deciding the fate of a fellow citizen. He must be allowed to",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      638.61,
      550.78,
      651.89
    ],
    "text": "understand he had a fair hearing. He must be satisfied that his side of the story, too, was heard.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      731.38,
      547.16,
      755.86
    ],
    "text": "Page 5 of 6",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      79.69,
      547.66,
      92.97
    ],
    "text": "It is up to the Appellant to give evidence or not. His silence without giving evidence himself is not",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      100.33,
      547.65,
      113.61
    ],
    "text": "a bar for him to call witnesses. The law requires that if he opts to give evidence, he must give",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      121.09,
      147.5,
      134.37
    ],
    "text": "evidence first.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      162.49,
      547.43,
      175.77
    ],
    "text": "For this inquiry to be fair, the Appellant should have had the opportunity to call his witness and",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      183.13,
      547.66,
      196.41
    ],
    "text": "establish his defence. According to the letter of the Secretary, there is no barrier to calling the",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      203.89,
      547.48,
      217.17
    ],
    "text": "witnesses; even though they are official witnesses, the decision of calling or not was in the hand",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      224.53,
      287.33,
      237.81
    ],
    "text": "of the inquiring officer. This denial is fatal.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      265.96,
      547.64,
      279.24
    ],
    "text": "As for recording the evidence of his wife should not have been allowed. The Evidence Ordinance",
