      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      452.34,
      407.59,
      465.62
    ],
    "text": "is now estopped from taking advantage of his wife giving evidence.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      493.74,
      547.34,
      507.02
    ],
    "text": "Even though a layman was in charge of the proceedings, inquiring Officer should have inquired",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      514.38,
      321.89,
      527.66
    ],
    "text": "whether there was an objection to calling the wife.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      555.78,
      547.64,
      569.06
    ],
    "text": "However, this point was not discussed by the High Court judge. A judicial officer must consider",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      576.54,
      547.64,
      589.82
    ],
    "text": "every aspect, especially when they are pleaded. Even if a particular point is not argued, the judge",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      597.21,
      547.57,
      610.49
    ],
    "text": "must consider, evaluate, and answer if that point is essential. Calling the wife, especially when a",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      617.97,
      547.6,
      631.25
    ],
    "text": "divorce case is pending, should have been considered by the High Court Judge. To the naked eye",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      638.61,
      547.61,
      651.89
    ],
    "text": "calling a spouse as a witness against the other spouse in any inquiry is beyond reason. Even in a",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      659.37,
      489.58,
      672.65
    ],
    "text": "court of law, a spouse is called only in instances provided for in Evidence Ordinance.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      731.38,
      547.16,
      755.86
    ],
    "text": "Page 6 of 6",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      79.69,
      547.64,
      92.97
    ],
    "text": "The final ground of not having evidence on the three counts found guilty is vague. Even if I hold",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      100.33,
      520.54,
      113.61
    ],
    "text": "with the Respondents on that ground, the Respondents will fail on not having a fair hearing.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      76.58,
      141.73,
      328.25,
      155.01
    ],
    "text": "For the reasons discussed above, I allow the appeal.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
